<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> New York Jets Waive Seven Players </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HEMPSTEAD, N.Y. (AP) -- Defensive end Mike Frederick, a four-year  
veteran signed as a free agent, was one of seven players waived by 
the New York Jets on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Jets still need to make one more cut to get down to the  
league-mandated 65-player limit by Tuesday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	Frederick spent his entire NFL career with the  
Cleveland-Baltimore franchise. A third-round pick in 1995 by the 
Browns, he moved with the team to Baltimore in 1996 and started 11 
games for the Ravens. 
</P>
<P>
	Also released was second-year guard Doug Karczewski, who was  
projected as a starter entering training camp. But the rapid 
development of three rookies left no room for him. 
</P>
<P>
	The other cuts were sixth-round pick Mark Megna, a linebacker;  
receivers Brian Musso and Joe Douglass; cornerback Del Lee, and 
fullback-tight end Jermaine Wiggins, both rookies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
