<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that are moving substantially or trading  
heavily today on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *Progressive Corp., down 18 1/2 at 100 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The insurer said late Friday it expects to miss analysts'  
third-quarter earnings estimates of $1.46 per share. Progressive 
officials cited price cuts and higher-than-expected claims. 

</P>
<P>
 *Republic Services Inc., down 5 3/8 at 11 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The company, an operator of waste collection services, said 1999  
earnings will miss analysts' forecast of $1.25 a share. Republic 
said it is taking longer than anticipated to integrate assets 
acquired from Waste Management Inc. 

</P>
<P>
 *Boeing Co., up 1 7/8 at 45 11/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Company officials are nearing agreement with leaders of its  
largest union on a three-year contract. If the contract is 
ratified, it would eliminate the threat of a strike that has hung 
over the company. 

</P>
<P>
 *Fair Isaac &AMP; Co., down 3 1/4 at 26 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	An analyst at U.S. Bancorp Piper Jaffray cut his rating on the  
stock from ``buy'' to ``neutral.'' Fair Isaac makes data management 
systems and software. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *Applix Inc., up 6 13/16 at 23 5/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Shares have risen as investors continue to see potential in  
companies offering products for the Linux computer operating 
system. Applix, based in Westboro, Mass., has a unit that offers 
products for the Linux operating system. 

</P>
<P>
 *Team America Corp., up 11/16 at 5 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The company received a revised buyout offer from an investor  
group that increases the suggested purchase price and extends the 
offer for 21 days. Team America provides human resource 
administration for small and medium-sized businesses. 

</P>
<P>
 *Corel Corp., up 1 at 6 5/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Corel, a maker of graphics and business productivity software,  
signed a deal to include reflective color reference targets made by 
Agfa Corp. with its products. 

</P>
<P>
 *Internet Capital Group, up 7 at 60 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	Merrill Lynch launched coverage of Internet Capital Group, a  
holding company involved in operating electronic commerce 
companies. Merrill gave the shares a long-term ``buy'' rating. 

</P>
<P>
 *Coulter Pharmaceutical Inc., down 10 15/16 at 23 1/2    	
</P>
<P>
	The U.S. Food and Drug Administration has requested a  
modification in its application to license a new cancer drug. 
Coulter filed an application with Smith-Kline Beecham PLC to 
license Bexxar, a treatment for low-grade B-cell non-Hodgkin's 
lymphoma. 





  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
