<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> CompUSA To Lay Off 1,800 in Sales </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- Personal computer and electronics retailer CompUSA  
is laying off about 1,800 people in a restructuring that will 
reduce its commercial sales force by half. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said that commercial sales representatives would be  
regionally based instead of working out of CompUSA stores, which 
led to duplication in markets where the chain has more than one 
store. The commercial sales organization will shrink from 3,600 to 
1,800, under the reorganization announced Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Spokeswoman Suzanne Shelton said 1,800 workers would be laid  
off. Of the remaining 1,800 sales employees, she said 1,300 have 
been offered positions elsewhere in the revamped operation, 
including in a new Dallas call center. 
</P>
<P>
	The call center will feature advanced telecommunications  
services in which sales agents will immediately be able to see the 
customer's account information. 
</P>
<P>
	The company said the change is designed to cut costs and provide  
specialized service for corporate, government and education 
customers. 





  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
