<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Lyndon LaRouche Story </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Associated Press reported erroneously Aug.  
18 in a story about Lyndon LaRouche that a convicted felon can't 
appear on the ballot in many states. The incorrect information came 
from the Federal Election Commission. 
</P>
<P>
	In fact, many states will not put imprisoned felons on the  
ballot but candidates with prior convictions are eligible. 
  	   	
