<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Marc Anthony Releases New Album </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN JUAN, Puerto Rico (AP) -- Marc Anthony says his new  
English-language album is ``just another way of expressing 
myself.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The salsa singer's foray into pop comes as another local  
favorite, Ricky Martin, continues to smash sales records with his 
own English debut. Martin is Puerto Rican, while Anthony was born 
in New York to Puerto Rican parents. 
</P>
<P>
	During a Monday visit to San Juan to promote the album's Sept.  
28 release, Anthony told reporters he was not abandoning fans of 
his three salsa records. 
</P>
<P>
	Anthony has sold three million albums in Spanish, and his  
``Contra la Corriente'' won a Grammy this year for best tropical 
Latin performance. 
</P>
<P>
	``This is just another way of expressing myself through my  
music,'' Anthony said. Recording in English, he said, ``is 
something I've always wanted to do.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Anthony said his next album will be in Spanish.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
