<HEADLINE> Rams Trade Mitch Jacoby to Chiefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. LOUIS (AP) -- The St. Louis Rams traded backup tight end  
Mitch Jacoby to the Kansas City Chiefs on Monday for an undisclosed 
draft pick. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rams also released 10 players, reducing the roster to 66.  
NFL teams must reduce their rosters to 65 by 4 p.m. EDT Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Among those cut was seventh-round draft pick Rodney Williams, a  
punter from Georgia Tech. 
</P>
<P>
	Jacoby, 6-foot-4 and 260 pounds, was used primarily on special  
teams by the Rams. He started two games in two seasons, catching 
two passes for 10 yards. He had 10 special-teams tackles in 1997, 
and three last season, when he played just five games after tearing 
a thumb ligament in the preseason. 
</P>
<P>
	The Rams also placed tight end Ernie Conwell and tackle Todd  
Frohbieter on the physically-unable-to-perform list. That means 
that after the sixth week of the season, the Rams will have 21 days 
to determine if the players should be placed on the active roster, 
on injured reserve, waived or traded. 
</P>
<P>
	St. Louis put quarterback Trent Green and center John Flannery  
on injured reserve. Both will miss the entire season. Green, signed 
as a free agent in the offseason, sustained a serious knee injury 
in Saturday's 24-21 preseason win over San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
	Green was 11-for-11 in the game and completed 28 of 32 preseason  
passes. 
</P>
<P>
	Other players cut Monday included wide receivers Tony Small and  
Daniel Jones; quarterback Gus Ornstein; defensive linemen Brian 
Lytle and Alton Weaver; safety Van Hiles, cornerbacks Marvin Love 
and Damon Troy; and tackle Roger Chanoine. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
