<HEADLINE> Edward Burns Working on a Script </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Edward Burns, best known for writing and  
starring in films about guys and girls, is working on a script 
about cops and criminals. 
</P>
<P>
	And Burns didn't have to look too far for advice. His father,  
Edward Burns Sr., is a retired police sergeant. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was a cop for 28 years in New York, so he's giving me notes  
on where I strayed from reality,'' Burns said in the Sept. 3 issue 
of Entertainment Weekly. 
</P>
<P>
	The writer-director-actor, who gained fame in ``The Brothers  
McMullen,'' ``She's the One'' and Steven Spielberg's ``Saving 
Private Ryan,'' will submit his new script to DreamWorks in 
September. ``On the Job'' is about two generations of 
Irish-American policemen. 
</P>
<P>
	So what does dad think?  
</P>
<P>
	``So far he loves it,'' Burns said.  
  	   	
</P>
