<HEADLINE> Mets' Alfonso Hits Three Homers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Edgardo Alfonzo hit three homers for the New York  
Mets on Monday night against the Houston Astros. 
</P>
<P>
	Alfonzo became the sixth Mets player to accomplish the feat --  
all on the road -- with a solo homer off Shane Reynolds in the 
first, a two-run shot off Brian Williams in the fourth and a 
leadoff homer in the sixth off Sean Bergman. 
</P>
<P>
	The second baseman also singled and scored a run in the second.  
</P>
<P>
	Alfonzo's 23 home runs are a Mets record for a second baseman in  
a season, surpassing Jeff Kent who hit 21 in 1993. 
</P>
<P>
	Gary Carter was the last Mets player to homer three times in a  
game when he did it at San Diego on Sept. 3, 1985. 
</P>
