<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Nilsson Injured for Rest of Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MILWAUKEE (AP) -- Milwaukee Brewers All-Star catcher David  
Nilsson will miss the rest of the season because of a broken thumb, 
a newspaper reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The catcher's teammates learned the news shortly before taking  
the field against the San Diego Padres on Sunday, the Milwaukee 
Journal Sentinel said in Monday's editions. The Brewers lost the 
game 5-4. 
</P>
<P>
	Nilsson was struck by a foul tip at the start of Saturday's game  
against the Padres. 
</P>
<P>
	The 29-year-old native of Brisbane, Australia, joined the  
Brewers in 1987 as an undrafted free agent. 
</P>
<P>
	Nilsson, the first Australian player ever to make a major league  
All-Star team, arranged his contract to become a free agent after 
this season. He is considering playing for Australia in next year's 
Summer Olympics in Sydney. 
</P>
<P>
	When he was named to the team in July, Nilsson was leading NL  
catchers with 19 homers to go with his .315 batting average and 51 
RBIs. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
