<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> NC State Victory Stuns Texas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AUSTIN, Texas (AP) -- Texas can forget about replacing Ricky  
Williams. The Longhorns have to worry about finding punt 
protection. 
</P>
<P>
	Despite a dominating defensive performance that held North  
Carolina State to 172 yards and one offensive score, Texas gave up 
a school-record three blocked punts that led to 16 points in the 
Wolfpack's 23-20 victory Saturday night in the Black Coaches 
Association Classic. 
</P>
<P>
	NC State returned two fourth-quarter blocks by freshman Terrence  
Holt for touchdowns. The Wolfpack could have scored another TD on a 
first-quarter block but three players couldn't pick up the ball 
before it rolled out of the back of the end zone for a safety. 
</P>
<P>
	The Longhorns were ranked 17th in the preseason Top 25 but  
dropped out Sunday night, replaced by North Carolina State, which 
moved into the rankings at No. 24. 
</P>
<P>
	Changes will be made on Texas' punt team, which had too many  
inexperienced players, coach Mack Brown said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've got reevaluate what we're doing there and how not to put  
those young guys in those tough spots,'' Brown said. ``We felt like 
we could block one of their punts. We didn't and they did.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Brown thought he solved one problem during the game. Figuring  
junior offensive lineman and long-snapper Marcel Blanchard was 
tiring, Brown replaced him with freshman Hunter McWilliams after 
the second block. McWilliams snapped the ball well on the final 
block but the protection broke down. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's something Stanford will try to exploit next weekend,''  
Brown said. ``We'll probably be nervous about it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	A season-opening loss was not what the Texas faithful had  
envisioned after a resurgent 9-3 campaign in 1998. More than 80,000 
packed Royal-Memorial Stadium to watch the continued rebirth of 
their once-dormant program. 
</P>
<P>
	They were stunned when Holt, younger brother of former Wolfpack  
All-America wideout Torry Holt, recorded his second block. Eric 
Leak picked up the loose ball and returned it for the winning 
touchdown with 3:22 to play. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's a devastating loss for our kids and our fans and I hate  
it,'' Brown said. ``Thank goodness it's the first game and not the 
last.'' 
</P>
<P>
	For North Carolina State, it was the third early season upset in  
as many years with victories over Syracuse in 1997 and Florida 
State last year. 
</P>
<P>
	Wolfpack players ran onto the field in celebration at the final  
gun. The victory left coach Mike O'Cain beaming about his team's 
rise from consecutive 3-8 seasons in 1995 and 1996. 
</P>
<P>
	``We were almost run out of Raleigh three years ago, and now we  
beat Texas on national TV,'' O'Cain said. 
</P>
<P>
	Offensively, the Wolfpack struggled. After giving up 99 yards in  
the first quarter, Texas' defense clamped down on the NC State 
running backs and quarterback Jamie Barnette. 
</P>
<P>
	The ACC's total offense leader in 1998, Barnette was 9-of-26 for  
65 yards with one interception. It was his worst outing as a 
starter as the offense totaled just seven first downs.. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm so grateful we won. So grateful,'' Barnette said. ``We  
can't play any worse that this on offense, and we still win the 
game.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
