<HEADLINE> Red Sox To Activate Ramon Martinez </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BOSTON (AP) -- Boston Red Sox pitcher Bret Saberhagen has a  
frayed rotator cuff, but he said Monday he will postpone surgery 
until after the season in the hopes that he can pitch again this 
year. 
</P>
<P>
	Also, Red Sox manager Jimy Williams said the team will activate  
Ramon Martinez from the 60-day disabled list to start on Thursday 
against Kansas City. 
</P>
<P>
	Saberhagen, 35, is 9-5 with a 3.36 ERA this season. The two-time  
Cy Young Award winner missed most of 1996-97 after unrelated 
surgery on his right shoulder. 
</P>
<P>
	Martinez, the older brother of Red Sox ace Pedro Martinez, has  
missed the entire season after right shoulder surgery. He has a 
123-77 record and 3.45 ERA in parts of 11 seasons with the Los 
Angeles Dodgers. 
  	   	
</P>
