<HEADLINE> Cop Taped Beating Man Pleads Guilty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- A police officer caught on  
videotape beating a handcuffed suspect pleaded guilty Monday to 
battery and was sentenced to a year of probation. 
</P>
<P>
	Stephen Danner, 33, was charged after a videotape was mailed  
anonymously to City Hall about two months after the Dec. 7 
incident. 
</P>
<P>
	The tape shows Danner, who has since been fired, swinging his  
baton over his head at least 16 times and striking 18-year-old 
David Weiler, who was lying handcuffed on the ground. 
</P>
<P>
	Weiler had resisted when officers tried to put him in a patrol  
car. He was not seriously injured. 
</P>
<P>
	Police had been called to the scene on a report of a bothersome  
stranger. Officers said it appeared Weiler was in the midst of a 
drug-induced psychosis. 
</P>
<P>
	His arrest and subsequent removal in an ambulance was filmed by  
someone who was in a nearby car. 
  	   	
</P>
