<HEADLINE> Giants Center Has Bone Bruise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Center Brian Williams, attempting a  
comeback after missing two seasons with an eye injury, only bruised 
his left knee in the New York Giants' preseason game with the New 
York Jets on Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams' did not practice on Monday, and his status for the  
Giants preseason finale at Baltimore is uncertain. 
</P>
<P>
	``I think the worst-case scenario is he misses this game,''  
Giants coach Jim Fassel said. ``That's great.'' 
</P>
<P>
	An 11-year veteran, Williams was injured in the second quarter  
in a knee-to-knee collision with one of the Jets' defensive linemen 
on a running play. He stayed in one more play, but then walked off 
the field. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was able to ride the (stationary) bike, but it's just hard  
to straighten out and I don't have a lot of flexibility,'' Williams 
said. 
</P>
<P>
	The Giants waived punter Brion Hurley, quarterback Steve Buck,  
receiver Anthony Tucker and running back Reynard Rutherford on 
Monday. Defensive end C.W. Estes, the former Army player who was 
sidelined the last two weeks with a foot injury, was cut after 
reaching an injury settlement. 
</P>
<P>
	Fullback Raymond Prister (foot) and cornerback Kelvin Suggs  
(knee) were placed on injured reserve. 
</P>
<P>
	The Giants have 72 players on the roster, but they won't have to  
make any more cuts until next week because they have seven NFL 
Europe roster exemptions. 
  	   	
</P>
