<HEADLINE> Volkswagen, Audi Recall 428,000 Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WOLFSBURG, Germany (AP) -- Volkswagen and its Audi subsidiary are  
recalling about 428,000 cars worldwide, all produced in the first 
half of 1998, due to a potential problem with the vehicles' 
steering mechanism, VW said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	The recall includes 270,000 VW Passats and 158,000 Audi A4, A6  
and A8 cars, said VW spokesman Jens Bobsien. 
</P>
<P>
	VW is sending letters to car owners instructing them to go to  
their dealer or mechanic to get the problem fixed at no charge as a 
precautionary measure. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been no known accidents as a result of the problem,  
Bobsien said. 
</P>
<P>
	Bobsien said the ``incomplete seal'' problem on the steering  
mechanism of the cars was discovered when some customers complained 
of a slight noise. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
