<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar Mixed; Gold Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mixed against other major  
currencies in European trading today. Gold prices fell. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0453 in late European trading, down  
from $1.0473 Friday. Later, in early afternoon trading in New York, 
the euro traded at $1.0452. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Friday,  
included 111.12 Japanese yen, down from 111.62; 1.5310 Swiss 
francs, up from 1.5288; 1.4879 Canadian dollars, down from 1.4942. 
</P>
<P>
	The British pound was quoted at $1.5878, up from $1.5876.  
</P>
<P>
	In early afternoon trading in New York, the dollar bought 110.97  
yen, and the pound was worth $1.5893. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar is worth 1.8711 German marks, up from 1.8675; 
6.2753 French francs, up from 6.2633; 2.1082 Dutch guilders, up 
from 2.1042; 1,852.36 Italian lire, up from 1,848.82. 
</P>
<P>
	The London gold and silver markets were closed for a holiday.  
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich the bid price was $253.05, down from $253.25.  
</P>
<P>
	Gold rose $0.20 in Hong Kong to close at $253.95.  
  	   	
