<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ravens Fine Missing McCrary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	OWINGS MILLS, Md. (AP) -- Baltimore Ravens Pro Bowl defensive end  
Michael McCrary missed practice Monday due to a contract dispute 
and will be fined by the team for every day he misses. 
</P>
<P>
	The 29-year-old McCrary, who is in the final year of his  
contract, left Saturday for his home in Phoenix after growing 
frustrated during his efforts to negotiate a contract extension. 
</P>
<P>
	Following practice Monday, Billick said the Ravens will not  
negotiate with McCrary or his agent until he returns to camp. 
</P>
<P>
	``We expect to be dealt with professionally,'' Billick said.  
``We want Michael to be here. I have no doubt in my mind that a 
deal will get done. But we are not going to negotiate with him not 
in camp.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McCrary, who had 14.5 sacks last season, wants a five- or  
six-year deal averaging $7 million a year, including a $13 million 
signing bonus, said his agent, Michael George. 
</P>
<P>
	George met with the Ravens last Friday. The team offered $36  
million over six years with an $11.5 million signing bonus, 
according to The (Baltimore) Sun. 
</P>
<P>
	George rejected it, saying it was below market value.  
</P>
<P>
	``The further this goes along, the further out of control this  
gets,'' George said. ``We're not trying to force them into anything 
except a fair-market deal.'' 
</P>
<P>
	McCrary has 35 sacks over his last 38 games and was elected to  
the Pro Bowl as a starter for the first time in his career last 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	But he hasn't played yet in a preseason game as he recovers from  
offseason knee surgery. He was scheduled to play in Friday's 
preseason finale against the New York Giants. 
</P>
<P>
	``It's not so much of a distraction,'' linebacker Peter Boulware  
said. ``We'd love to have him here, he really helps our defense. 
But we can't get down because of it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Billick's reaction was similar.  
</P>
<P>
	``I know it's preseason but we're 3-0 and the guys are playing  
hard and he hasn't had a snap yet,'' Billick said. ``Michael 
McCrary is a major part of this football team. He's a major asset 
for us. He is not here right now. He is not a major part of what 
we're doing right now.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
