<HEADLINE> Liz Taylor Released From Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Elizabeth Taylor has been released from a  
hospital where she was treated for a back injury following a fall. 
</P>
<P>
	The 67-year-old actress went home from Cedars-Sinai Medical  
Center on Sunday, spokesman Warren Cowan said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Miss Taylor was recovering well from a compression fracture of a  
vertebra and undergoing physical therapy at home, Cowan said. Her 
recovery was expected to take several weeks. 
</P>
<P>
	The actress suffered the injury in a fall at her Bel Air home  
Aug. 19. 
  	   	
