<HEADLINE> U.S. Soccer Group Invites Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- The U.S. Soccer Federation invited Iran to play a  
match in the United States, a spokesman said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	``There have been ongoing discussions between the two  
federations,'' spokesman Brian Remedi of the U.S. Soccer Federation 
said. ``We would like to play a match in the U.S. sometime next 
year.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Remedi said the Iran-U.S. match in the 1998 World Cup was a good  
one and the federation would like to have the U.S. team play the 
Iranians again. Iran eliminated the United States from the World 
Cup with a 2-1 victory. 
</P>
<P>
	An exchange of gifts between players from the two teams that day  
won the countries the 1998 fair-play prize from world soccer's 
governing body, FIFA. 
</P>
<P>
	Remedi said talks were still preliminary.  
  	   	
</P>
