rookie Jason Ryan to beat the Minnesota Twins 2-1 Monday night. 
Hentgen allowed just one run and five hits in 7 1-3 innings as 
Toronto stopped a nine-game home losing streak, the second-longest 
home skid in team history. 

</P>
