<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> AmSouth, First American Merger Ok'd </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Federal Reserve has approved the $5  
billion merger of AmSouth Bancorp. and First American Corp. 
</P>
<P>
	The central bank's board of governors on Monday voted 3-0 to  
approve the merger, which will create a bank company with $40.6 
billion in assets operating in Alabama, Arkansas, Georgia, Florida, 
Kentucky, Louisiana, Mississippi, Tennessee and Virginia. 
</P>
<P>
	The new company, to be called AmSouth Bancorp., will be the  
nation's 22nd-largest bank, according to the Fed. Its headquarters 
will be in Birmingham, Ala., where AmSouth currently is based. 
</P>
<P>
	The transaction is expected to be completed by Oct. 1 and the  
companies plan to merge their operations in mid-February. 
</P>
<P>
	First American employs about 7,200 people, including some 3,300  
in Nashville, where it is based. It has about 390 offices. 
</P>
<P>
	AmSouth has some 6,700 employees in 290 offices.  




  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
