<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Japan's Auto Production Falls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japan's auto production fell for the fourth month  
in a row in July, registering a 3.6 percent decline from a year 
earlier. 
</P>
<P>
	A total of 887,288 cars, trucks and buses rolled off the  
assembly lines last month, compared with 920,776 a year ago, the 
Japan Automobile Manufacturers' Association said Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	It attributed the fall to continued sluggish consumer demand for  
big-ticket items and falling exports. The association estimated 
vehicle exports in July fell 10 percent. It will release complete 
figures later this month. 
</P>
<P>
	The July drop in production follows a 2.5 percent decline in  
June, a 2.4 percent decline in May and a 6.5 percent tumble in 
April. 
</P>
<P>
	Domestic vehicle demand in July totaled 537,616, down 3.8  
percent from a year earlier, the group said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
