<DOCNO> APW19990830.0207 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-08-30 13:30:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Monica Lewinsky Selling Handbags </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Monica Lewinsky's still looking for that perfect  
job, but in the meantime she's hoping to make money selling her own 
line of handbags over the Internet. 
</P>
<P>
	``What really excites me is that this has nothing to do with the  
president,'' she said in October's Marie Claire magazine. 
</P>
<P>
	The former White House intern is selling eight designs, ranging  
from $70 to $130. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lewinsky said she took up knitting and sewing ``as the only  
way to stay sane'' when she was holed up in her Washington 
apartment, forbidden by prosecutors to talk to anyone by phone or 
e-mail. After she made her first handbag, all her friends wanted 
one. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
