<HEADLINE> Japan's Jobless Rate at Record High </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	TOKYO (AP) -- Japan's jobless rate in July remained at the  
previous month's record high 4.9 percent, the government announced 
Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The unemployment rate has worsened in recent months, increasing  
pessimism about the nation's economy, which is struggling through 
its worst downturn in 50 years. 
</P>
<P>
	Economists surveyed by Dow Jones Newswires in Tokyo had forecast  
the overall jobless rate would stay at 4.9 percent in July. 
</P>
<P>
	The unemployment rate for men stayed at 5.1 percent, also a  
record high. The rate was also unchanged for women at 4.6 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	The overall jobless rate stood at 4.8 percent in March and April  
before improving to 4.6 percent in May. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
