<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Brewers Place Nilsson on DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- All-Star catcher David Nilsson, who broke his  
right thumb during a game at San Diego last weekend, was put on the 
15-day disabled list Monday by the Milwaukee Brewers. 
</P>
<P>
	Nilsson, 30, was hurt when hit by a foul tip in the first inning  
Saturday. He was batting .311 with 21 home runs and 62 RBIs through 
112 games this season. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's a chance he'll come back for the last two weeks, but  
we'll see,'' Brewers manager Jim Lefebvre said. ``We don't know how 
it's going to heal or whatever the situation is. They said it's a 
two-to-three-week situation, so we're just going to play it by 
ear.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Milwaukee recalled catcher/infielder Brian Banks from Triple-A  
Louisville. Banks, 28, spent most of the season with the Brewers 
and was sent down Aug. 20 when Jeromy Burnitz was activated from 
the DL. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
