<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Arab Games Roundup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	AMMAN, Jordan (AP) -- Egypt won three more events on Monday to  
finish on top with 105 gold medals at the Arab Games, which were 
marred by confusion, disorganization and missed schedules. 
</P>
<P>
	Tunisia finished second with 40 golds, while Algeria was third  
with 34, according to unofficial tallies. Organizers have rarely 
provided official results until several hours after the day's 
events. 
</P>
<P>
	Egypt won 20 swimming races, including 10 by Rania Alwani, a  
U.S. medical student. 
</P>
<P>
	The games were marked by unprecedented violence when Libyan  
soccer fans rioted at two matches. Players complained about 
refereeing and lack of facilities. 
</P>
<P>
	After officials announced earlier this week that six  
bodybuilders had been disqualified, organizers two days later 
mentioned only five athletes and gave a different nationality for 
one of them. There was no clarification as to which version was 
correct. 
</P>
<P>
	An unofficial tally shows Egypt will end with 105 gold medals,  
79 silvers and 79 bronzes. Tunisia is second with 40 golds, 40 
silvers and 57 bronzes, and Algeria third with 34 golds, 31 silver 
and 35 bronze. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
