<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Gains 25 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- The Dow Jones industrial average is up 25 points  
in today's early going. Advancers on the New York Stock Exchange 
hold a 6-5 ead over decliners. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is up two points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is up one point. 
</P>
<P>
	Wall Street appears to be in no hurry to recover the ground that  
was lost the past two sessions. 
</P>
<P>
	The Dow finished last week with losses of more than 100 points  
on both Thursday and Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Friday's loss came after Fed chairman Alan Greenspan suggested  
that central bankers need to pay closer attention to market 
fluctuations. 
</P>
<P>
	Like Friday, trading volume is expected to remain rather light  
today. 
</P>
<P>
	There is an economic report to consider. The July report on new  
home sales is to be released at 10 a.m. EDT. 
</P>
<P>
	Ahead of the report, bonds are flat to slightly higher in price.  
</P>
</TEXT>
